SIMPLE: suffusion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffusion
<hw>Suf*fu"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suffusio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>suffusion</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of suffusing, or state of being suffused; an
overspreading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To those that have the jaundice, or like <qex>suffusion</qex> of
eyes, objects appear of that color.</q> <rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That with which a thing is suffused.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A blending of one color into
another; the spreading of one color over another, as on the feathers of
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sufi</ent>⟦br⟧
